		<title>02Gwennap Pit</title>
		<content> Gwennap Pit is famous amongst         
 Methodists throughout the world as one
 of John Wesley's principal preaching  
 centres. He first visited here in     
 September 1762 and described it as    
 "far the finest (natural amphitheatre)
 I know in the kingdom".It was formed  
 when underground mine workings        
 subsided and later the sides were     
 terraced and levelled. An annual      
 service has been held on Whit. Monday 
 ever since Wesley's death.            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
